description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for an Occupational Therapist who would like to develop their skills as a Specialist OT. We have 0.6 WTE post / 3 days available for the successful candidates to join our enthusiastic and supportive Children’s Integrated Therapy (CIT) Team, providing an innovative service to children in Barnet. We are proud to be part of NELFT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service offers ongoing development opportunities including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peer Supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Twilight Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical and Management Supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shadowing opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Service and Trust Induction Packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialist advice and second opinions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Appraisals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;joint working with colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition you will be supported with your own clinical interests and engage in team projects co-working with other colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your key responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working within one or more integrated Pathways:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motor Skills Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute / Sensory Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex Specific Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social Communication Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritisation, Assessment and Therapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting children’s and young people’s Occupational Performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with children in groups and individually.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as part of a multi-professional team in partnership with families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training families and professionals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jointly setting and reviewing targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application as the first step towards welcoming you to the Barnet CIT Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMarion NeumanJob titleClinical Team Lead, CITEmail addressmarion.neuman@nelft.nhs.ukTelephone number 0300 300 1821&lt;/p&gt;
